replies.body:
For me, the game died a long time ago when they "reworked" Cassiopeia in season 4.{{champion:69}}

That being said, there's the main issue of far too many games ending in extremely onesided curbstomps which only leaves players frustrated. Giving first blood is all it needs to know what kind of flow the game is going to take on. 

The snowballing mechanics need to be toned down and towers massively buffed if they expect anyone to put up with this inherently frustrating gameplay. They seriously should consider implementing a surrender option after 15 minutes at this point.
